                    <div class="comparison-item legacy">
                      <h3>OpenVPN Security Model</h3>
                      <p>OpenVPN uses legacy TLS/SSL with configurable cipher suites, creating complexity and potential misconfiguration risks.</p>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Multiple cipher options (easy to misconfigure)</li>
                        <li>Complex certificate management</li>
                        <li>Large attack surface (100k+ LOC)</li>
                        <li>Stateful connections (vulnerable to attacks)</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="comparison-item modern">
                      <h3>Defguard Security Model</h3>
                      <p>WireGuard uses modern, fixed cryptographic primitives with no configuration options—eliminating misconfiguration vulnerabilities.</p>
                      <ul>
                        <li>Fixed modern cryptography (ChaCha20, Curve25519)</li>
                        <li>Simple key exchange (no PKI complexity)</li>
                        <li>Minimal attack surface (~4k LOC)</li>
                        <li>Stateless design (cryptokey routing)</li>
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
